sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client<br/>(KServe Proxy / User)
    participant KServeGW as KServe Gateway<br/>(Ingress managed)
    participant API as vLLM OpenAI API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP(S)
    participant Engine as vLLM Engine (V1)<br/>Continuous Batching
    participant HFHub as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PVC as Local PVC<br/>Filesystem
    participant Prom as Prometheus

    Note over Client,PVC: Flow 1: Model Inference Request

    Client->>KServeGW: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer API Key
    KServeGW->>API: Forward request<br/>HTTP 8000/TCP<br/>TLS optional

    Note over Engine,PVC: Model Loading (first request or startup)
    alt Model from HuggingFace
        Engine->>HFHub: Download model weights<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>Auth: HF_TOKEN
        HFHub-->>Engine: Model artifacts
    else Model from S3
        Engine->>S3: Load model weights<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>Auth: AWS IAM (S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID)
        S3-->>Engine: Model artifacts
    else Model from PVC
        Engine->>PVC: Read model weights<br/>Filesystem
        PVC-->>Engine: Model artifacts
    end

    API->>Engine: Inference request<br/>(continuous batching)
    Note over Engine: CPU Attention Kernels<br/>KV Cache Management<br/>Quantization (INT4/INT8/FP8)
    Engine-->>API: Generated tokens<br/>(streaming or batch)
    API-->>KServeGW: JSON Response<br/>or SSE stream
    KServeGW-->>Client: Response

    Note over Prom,API: Flow 2: Prometheus Metrics Scraping

    Prom->>API: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP 8000/TCP<br/>No Auth
    API-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics<br/>(token throughput, batch sizes,<br/>cache utilization)

    Note over Client,API: Flow 3: Health Probes

    Client->>API: GET /health<br/>HTTP 8000/TCP<br/>No Auth
    API-->>Client: 200 OK (healthy)
